This place is a favorite and a must visit when in Chinatown.  The Thai restaurant I know that serves their food plate lunch style instead of family style and so affordable. First timers should try the chicken curry and garlic chicken plate with brown rice.  The curry is not too spicy, the garlic chicken is fragrant and crispy, the brown is not your usual brown rice but a special blend.  Then try the pad thai with garlic chicken.  Don't forget to also get their own version is summer rolls made with tuna. The couple who runs the restaurant are friendly and  hard working.

This place has the best garlic chicken. It is sooooo ono. Not the best place for Thai food, but the Vietnamese food is very good.  Definitely go for the garlic chicken though.

In heart of downtown Honolulu on Fort Street Mall.  Been going here for about 7 years and can't believe I haven't given a review yet.  Food is really good.  Pad Thai, Garlic Chicken, Green Curry with Chicken (Thursday and Friday Only) are my staples every time I go. Red curry is also the special but the green is better in my opinion.Just tried the Thai iced coffee and it was light in flavor and tasty.  If you want a strong coffee flavor this is probably not your speed.  They now offer Bahn Mi sandwiches so I will have to try that next.  Pho is good but not like LA or Bay Area which is legit.  BTW garlic chicken does not taste the same the next day but it still good.  Noodles and fried rice are still good the next day. skip the fried rolls as they are good but not very meaty.  Owners are friendly and they man the cash register and take you orders.   If you are in downtown, you should stop by.

The best garlic chicken is found here. This is a popular lunch spot for people who work in downtown Honolulu and for HPU students. If you go between 12pm-12:30pm, you'll see a line coming out the door. There is seating inside and outside but most people do take out. The mini garlic chicken plate is $8 but you can kick it up a notch by getting "garlic chicken with pad thai" or "garlic chicken with penang curry and rice" for a few more bucks.
